<LP>
   MAXWELL: Media executive Robert Maxwell signed an
agreement with West Germany's Gruner &amp; Jahr AG to acquire
Berliner Verlag, East Germany's largest newspaper and
magazine publisher. Mr. Maxwell's Mirror Group Newspapers
would operate the publisher in a joint venture with Gruner &amp;
Jahr, a unit of Bertlesmann AG. Terms weren't disclosed.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   MAGAZINES: McGraw-Hill Inc. acquired Southwest Contractor
magazine from Akers-Runbeck Publishing Co., Phoenix, Ariz.,
and Louisiana Contractor magazine from Rhodes Publishing Co.,
Baton Rouge, La. The prices weren't disclosed.
                                                                                                       

   WHO'S NEWS: Advance Publications named Simon Master
executive vice president, international, of its Random House
Inc. subsidiary. He remains deputy chairman of Random Century
Group in London while assuming responsibility for all
international operations. . . . Sony Corp.'s Columbia
Pictures Entertainment Co. subsidiary named Steven Mendelson
senior vice president of comedy development at Columbia
Pictures Television. He was vice president of comedy
development.
